Certainly! Here is the code for the `Solution` class seen in the image:

```java
class Solution {
    public boolean judgeCircle(String moves) {
        int x = 0;
        int y = 0;
        for (char move : moves.toCharArray()) {
            if (move == 'U') {
                y += 1;
            } else if (move == 'D') {
                y -= 1;
            } else if (move == 'L') {
                x -= 1;
            } else if (move == 'R') {
                x += 1;
            }
        }
        return (x == 0 && y == 0);
    }
}
```

This Java code is for a problem where you need to determine if a series of moves will return a robot to its original position on a grid. The robot can move up ('U'), down ('D'), left ('L'), or right ('R'). The `judgeCircle` method checks if the movements cancel out, leaving the robot back at the origin (0,0).
